Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Bring a #large saucepan{} of @water{for the pasta} to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the pasta. Trim the @green beans{80%g}. Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}.

Pop the tomatoes onto a piece of #foil{}. Drizzle over some @olive oil{}. Season with @salt{}, @pepper{} and the @sugar{1/2%tsp}. Fold the foil, sealing on all sides to create a parcel, then place onto a #small baking tray{}. When the oven is hot, roast the tomatoes on the top shelf until softened, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} to your pan of boiling water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}. Halfway through, add the green beans to the pasta and cook for the remaining time until tender, ~{5-6%minutes}.

While the pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on medium heat. Once hot, add the garlic and stir-fry for ~{1%minute}. Stir in the @water{150%ml} for the sauce and @vegetable stock paste{10%g}. Bring to the boil, then simmer until slightly reduced, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once reduced, stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g}, bring back to the boil, then remove from the heat. Taste and add @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

When the pasta and green beans have 3 mins left to cook, add the @peas{120%g} and simmer for ~{2-3%minutes}. Once cooked, drain the pasta and veg in a #colander{}, then add to the pan of sauce and heat through.

Stir through the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}, then taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of @water{} if you feel it needs it.

When everything's piping hot, spoon the pasta into your #bowls{} and drizzle over the @fresh pesto{50%g}. Carefully remove your roasted tomatoes from the foil and serve them on top. Spoon over the tomato juices from the parcel to finish. Enjoy!